-- Wendel reaps 1 bln eur from Saint-Gobain stake sale
-- By James Regan
-- Wed May 07, 2014 03:09AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, May 7 (Reuters) - French investment group Wendel <MWDP.PA> said it raised about 1 billion euros ($1.39 billion) from the sale of a 4.3 percent stake in Saint-Gobain <SGOB.PA>, Europe's biggest supplier of construction materials.

Wendel said it retained a stake of approximately 12 percent in Saint-Gobain's share capital and 20 percent of its voting rights.